channel.title: Could Axoloti fry my mixer channels
channel.description: Yesterday I was connecting my axoloti to my home studio for the first time. After fiddling arround a bit to get it working I noticed that I lost one of my mixer channels. Could this be caused by the axoloti? The axoloti seem to work fine although I had a screaming sound at one time in the process. I did disconnect the audio out once or twice while the axoloti was powered. Any thoughts.
